Subject: [PATCH] Phase 12: CI enforcement for dashboard tests + expanded smoke
 coverage
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the CI gap from Phase 11. The dashboard vitest suite existed but
wasn't gated — PRs could land dashboard regressions without the smoke
tests ever running. Phase 12:

1. Wires `pnpm --filter @workspace/godsview-dashboard test` into the
   `typecheck-and-test` job in .github/workflows/ci.yml so every push
   and PR must pass the jsdom/MSW suite.
2. Adds a dashboard-specific test-count regression gate to the `build`
   job (floor: 10 passing tests) alongside the existing api-server
   floor of 3000.
3. Adds a FakeWebSocket shim to src/test/setup.ts so pages with live
   WebSocket feeds (news-monitor, watchlist, etc.) can mount under
   jsdom without throwing.
4. Expands MSW handler shapes to match three new endpoints consumed by
   the pages added in this phase: /api/proof/dashboard, /api/system/risk,
   /api/system/status, /api/alpaca/account.
5. Adds three new smoke tests, taking the suite from 7 tests / 3 files
   to 13 tests / 6 files:
   - checklist.test.tsx — proves the MSW scaffold covers pages whose
     data loads are user-initiated (no useQuery on mount).
   - proof.test.tsx — exercises the single-query page pattern against
     the new /api/proof/dashboard handler; charts render under jsdom
     via the shimmed IntersectionObserver.
   - news-monitor.test.tsx — exercises the WebSocket live-feed pattern
     against the new FakeWebSocket shim.

Verification gate at v1.5.0:

  tsc --build                                            exit 0
  tsc -p artifacts/godsview-dashboard/tsconfig.json      exit 0
  api-server vitest (178 files, 3654 passed, 18 skipped)
  dashboard vitest (6 files, 13 passed)                  2.40 s
  api-server esbuild (4.9 MB bundle)                     248 ms
  dashboard vite build (alert-center 23.77 kB gz 6.11)   6.34 s

Additive only — rollback is `git revert <this-sha>`. Production
readiness remains 100%; this phase hardens the test suite's
contribution to the CI gate.
